                    412

                    413
                    
                    
                      
#' `r lifecycle::badge('experimental')`

                    415
                    
                    
                      
#' @param object A [trial_sequence] object.

                    		
                  

                  

                    416
                    
                    
                      
#' @param numerator Right hand side formula for the numerator model

                    		
                  

                  

                    417
                    
                    
                      
#' @param denominator Right hand side formula for the denominator model

                    		
                  

                  

                    418

                    420

                    421
                    
                    
                      
#' @param eligible_wts_1 Exclude some observations when fitting the models for the inverse probability of treatment

                    		
                  

                  

                    422
                    
                    
                      
#'   weights. For example, if it is assumed that an individual will stay on treatment for at least 2 visits, the first 2

                    		
                  

                  

                    423

                    424

                    425

                    426

                    427
                    
                    
                      
#'   definitions are applied to `eligible_wts_0` for excluding observations when fitting the models for the inverse

                    		
                  

                  

                    428
                    
                    
                      
#'   probability of treatment weights for those who are not on treatment at the immediately previous visit.

                    		
                  

                  

                    429
                    
                    
                      
#' @param ... Other arguments used by methods.

                    		
                  

                  

                    430

                    431

#' @include trial_sequence.R generics.R

#' Fit the marginal structural model for the sequence of emulated trials

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' `r lifecycle::badge('stable')`

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' Apply a weighted pooled logistic regression to fit the marginal structural model for the sequence of emulated trials

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' and calculates the robust covariance matrix  of parameter using the sandwich estimator.

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' @param use_sample_weights Use case-control sampling weights in addition to inverse probability weights for treatment

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#'   and censoring. `data` must contain a column `sample_weight`. The final weights used in the pooled logistic

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#'   regression are calculated as `weight = weight * sample_weight`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' @inheritParams initiators

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#' @details The model formula is constructed by combining the arguments `outcome_cov`, `model_var`,

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#' `include_followup_time`, and `include_trial_period`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#' @returns Object of class `TE_msm` containing

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#' \describe{

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#'  \item{model}{a `glm` object}

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#'  \item{robust}{a list containing a summary table of estimated regression coefficients and the robust covariance

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#'  matrix}

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#'  \item{args}{a list contain the parameters used to prepare and fit the model}

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#' }

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom stats as.formula binomial pnorm quantile relevel

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom utils write.csv

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    31

#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    515
                    
                    
                      
#' `r lifecycle::badge('stable')`

                    		
                  

                  

                    516
                    
                    
                      
#' This function predicts the marginal cumulative incidences when a target trial population receives either the

                    		
                  

                  

                    517
                    
                    
                      
#' treatment or non-treatment at baseline (for an intention-to-treat analysis) or either sustained treatment or

                    		
                  

                  

                    518
                    
                    
                      
#' sustained non-treatment (for a per-protocol analysis). The difference between these cumulative incidences is the

                    		
                  

                  

                    519
                    
                    
                      
#' estimated causal effect of treatment. Currently, the `predict` function only provides marginal intention-to-treat and

                    		
                  

                  

                    520
                    
                    
                      
#' per-protocol effects, therefore it is only valid when `estimand_type = "ITT"` or `estimand_type = "PP"`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    521
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    522
                    
                    
                      
#' @param object Object from [trial_msm()] or [initiators()] or [trial_sequence].

                    		
                  

                  

                    523
                    
                    
                      
#' @param newdata Baseline trial data that characterise the target trial population that marginal cumulative incidences

                    		
                  

                  

                    524
                    
                    
                      
#'   or survival probabilities are predicted for.  `newdata` must have the same columns and formats of variables as in

                    		
                  

                  

                    525
                    
                    
                      
#'   the fitted marginal structural model specified in [trial_msm()] or [initiators()]. If `newdata` contains rows with

                    		
                  

                  

                    526
                    
                    
                      
#'   `followup_time > 0` these will be removed.

                    		
                  

                  

                    527
                    
                    
                      
#' @param type Specify cumulative incidences or survival probabilities to be predicted. Either cumulative incidence

                    		
                  

                  

                    528
                    
                    
                      
#'   (`"cum_inc"`) or survival probability (`"survival"`).

                    		
                  

                  

                    529
                    
                    
                      
#' @param predict_times Specify the follow-up visits/times where the marginal cumulative incidences or survival

                    		
                  

                  

                    530
                    
                    
                      
#'   probabilities are predicted.

                    		
                  

                  

                    531
                    
                    
                      
#' @param conf_int Construct the point-wise 95-percent confidence intervals of cumulative incidences for the target

                    		
                  

                  

                    532
                    
                    
                      
#'   trial population under treatment and non-treatment and their differences by simulating the parameters in the

                    		
                  

                  

                    533
                    
                    
                      
#'   marginal structural model from a multivariate normal distribution with the mean equal to the marginal structural

                    		
                  

                  

                    534
                    
                    
                      
#'   model parameter estimates and the variance equal to the estimated robust covariance matrix.

                    		
                  

                  

                    535
                    
                    
                      
#' @param samples Number of samples used to construct the simulation-based confidence intervals.

                    		
                  

                  

                    536
                    
                    
                      
#' @param ... Further arguments passed to or from other methods.

                    		
                  

                  

                    537
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    538
                    
                    
                      
#' @return A list of three data frames containing the cumulative incidences for each of the assigned treatment options

                    		
                  

                  

                    539
                    
                    
                      
#'   (treatment and non-treatment) and the difference between them.

                    		
                  

                  

                    540
                    
                    
                      
#' @name predict_marginal

                    		
                  

                  

                    541
                    
                    
                      
#' @aliases predict

                    		
                  

                  

                    542
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    543
                    
                    
                      
setGeneric("predict", def = function(object, ...) standardGeneric("predict"))

                    		
                  

                
              

            

            

              

                
                  

                    1

                    8
                    4x

                    4x

  }

  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    18

#' P99 Weights Function

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' This function truncate the weights of data at the 1st and 99th percentile

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' @param weight The data.table weight column

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' @noRd

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
p99_weight <- function(weight) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    1x
                    
                      
  p99 <- quantile(weight, prob = c(0.01, 0.99), type = 1)

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    1x
                    
                      
  limit_weight(weight, p99[1], p99[2])

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' Limit Weights Function

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' This function truncate the weights using user defined limits

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' @param weight The data.table weight column

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#' @param lower_limit The user defined minimum possible weight

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#' @param upper_limit The user defined maximum possible weight

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#' @noRd

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
limit_weight <- function(weight, lower_limit, upper_limit) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    2x
                    
                      
  weight[weight > upper_limit] <- upper_limit

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    2x
                    
                      
  weight[weight < lower_limit] <- lower_limit

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    2x
                    
                      
  weight

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
}

#' Fit a GLM

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#' @param formula the model formula.

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
#' @param data a data frame or similar.

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
#' @param ... Other arguments for glm

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
#' @param glm_function The glm function to call given as a string, such as `"glm"` or `"parglm"`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
#' @noRd

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
#' @import parglm

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
#' @details

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
#' If no family is specified `binomial("logit")` will be used. If `glm_function = "parglm"` is specified

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
#' but no `nthreads`, `control`, or `method`, then the default is used

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      
#' `control = parglm.control(nthreads = 4, method = \"FAST\")`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
fit_glm <- function(formula, data, weights, ..., glm_function = "glm") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    76x
                    
                      
  this_call <- match.call(expand.dots = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    76x
                    
                      
  dots <- list(...)

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    76x
                    
                      
  this_call$`...` <- NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    76x
                    
                      
  this_call$glm_function <- NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    76x
                    
                      
  if (is.null(this_call$family)) this_call$family <- quote(binomial(link = "logit"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    76x
                    
                      
  this_call$formula <- formula

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    76x
                    
                      
  this_call$data <- quote(data)

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    76x
                    
                      
  if (glm_function == "parglm") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    14x
                    
                      
    if (!any(c("nthreads", "control", "method") %in% names(dots))) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    1x
                    
                      
      warning(

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    1x
                    
                      
        "Argument glm_function = \"parglm\" but no `nthreads`, `method` or `control` specified.\n",

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    1x
                    
                      
        "Using `control = parglm.control(nthreads = 4, method = \"FAST\")`"

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    
                    
                      
      )

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    1x
                    
                      
      this_call$control <- parglm::parglm.control(nthreads = 4, method = "FAST")

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    76x
                    
                      
  this_call[[1]] <- call(glm_function)[[1]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    76x
                    
                      
  for (i in names(dots)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    15x
                    
                      
    this_call[[i]] <- dots[[i]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    76x
                    
                      
  eval(this_call)

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    
                    
                      
}

#' Data Manipulation Function

                    50x

                    50x

                    50x

                    50x

                    1x

                    50x

                    1x

                    50x

                    43
                    50x

                    44
                    50x

                    50x

                    50x

                    50x

                    48
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    50x

                    50x

                    50x

                    50x

                    50x

                    50x

                    21x

                    21x
                    
                      
    sw_data[, eligible1_sw := NA_real_]

#' Prepare data for the sequence of emulated target trials

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' `r lifecycle::badge('stable')`

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' This function  expands observational data in the person-time format (i.e., the  `long' format) to emulate a sequence

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' of target trials and also estimates the inverse probability of treatment and censoring weights as required.

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' @inheritParams initiators

                    		
                  

                  

                    9

                    10

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' @param data_dir Directory to save model objects when `save_weight_models=TRUE` and expanded data as separate CSV

                    		
                  

                  

                    12

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#'   created. If the directory already contains trial files, an error will occur, other files may be overwritten.

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#' @details The arguments `chunk_size` and `separate_files` allow for processing of large datasets that would not fit in

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#' memory once expanded. When `separate_files = TRUE`, the input data are processed in chunks of individuals and saved

                    		
                  

                  

                    18

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#' a reduced dataset for the modelling.

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#' @returns An object of class `TE_data_prep`, which can either be sampled from ([case_control_sampling_trials]) or

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#'   directly used in a model ([trial_msm]). It contains the elements

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#' \describe{

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item{data}{the expanded dataset for all emulated trials. If `separate_files = FALSE`, it is  a `data.table`; if

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#'   `separate_files = TRUE`, it is a character vector with the file path of the expanded data as CSV files.}

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item{min_period}{index for the first trial in the expanded data}

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item{max_period}{index for the last trial in the expanded data}

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item{N}{the total number of observations in the expanded data}

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item{data_template}{a zero-row `data.frame`  with the columns and attributes of the expanded data}

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item{switch_models}{a list of summaries of the models fitted for inverse probability of treatment weights,

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
#'   if `estimand_type` is `"PP"` or `"As-Treated"`}

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item{censor_models}{a list of summaries of the models fitted for inverse probability of censoring weights,

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
#'   if `use_censor_weights=TRUE`}

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
#'  \item{args}{a list contain the parameters used to prepare the data and fit the weight models}

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
#'   }

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    37

#' Data Extension

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' Expands the longitudinal data into a sequence of trials.

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' @param data A `data.table` to be expanded

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' @param keeplist A list contains names of variables used in final model

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' @param outcome_cov A formula for covariate adjustment of the outcome model

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' @param first_period First period value to start expanding about

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' @param last_period Last period value to expand about

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' @param censor_at_switch Use censoring for per-protocol analysis - censor person-times once a person-trial

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' stops taking the initial treatment value

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#' @param where_var Variables used in where conditions used in subsetting the data used in final analysis (where_case),

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#'  the variables not included in the final model

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' @param data_dir Directory to save data

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#' @param separate_files Save expanded data in separate CSV files for each trial.

                    		
                  

                  

                    16

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#' @noRd

data_extension <- function(data,

                    		
                  

                  

                    20

                           outcome_cov = NA,

                    28
                    
                    
                      
                           chunk_size = 200) {

                    13x

      data = files[file.exists(files)],

      outcomeCov_var = outcomeCov_var,

#' Expand Function

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    
                    
                      
#' This function performs the data expansion for a given dataset

#'

#' the variables not included in the final model

#' Translate subset_condition to SQL syntax

                    		
                  

                  

                    142
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    143
                    
                    
                      
#' @param string subset_condition as a string

translate_to_sql <- function(string) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    149
                    3x
                    
                      
  tryCatch(

                    		
                  

                  

                    150
                    
                    
                      
    {

                    		
                  

                  

                    151
                    3x
                    
                      
      replacement <- c("\\|" = "OR", "&" = "AND", "==" = "=", "%in%" = "IN", "^c\\(" = "\\(")

                    		
                  

                  

                    152
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    153
                    3x
                    
                      
      vec <- strsplit(string, " ")[[1]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    154
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    155
                    3x
                    
                      
      if (length(grep(":", vec)) != 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    156
                    2x
                    
                      
        vec <- translate_num_vec(vec)

                    		
                  

                  

                    157
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    158
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    159
                    2x
                    
                      
      for (i in seq_len(length(replacement))) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    160
                    10x
                    
                      
        vec <- gsub(pattern = names(replacement)[i], replacement = replacement[i], vec)

                    		
                  

                  

                    161
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    162
                    2x
                    
                      
      string <- paste0(vec, collapse = " ")

                    		
                  

                  

                    163
                    2x
                    
                      
      string

                    		
                  

                  

                    164
                    
                    
                      
    },

                    		
                  

                  

                    165
                    3x
                    
                      
    error = function(e) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    166
                    1x
                    
                      
      stop("Error translating subset_condition to SQL. See ?sample_controls for me information.\n",

                    		
                  

                  

                    167
                    1x
                    
                      
        as.character(e),

                    		
                  

                  

                    168
                    1x
                    
                      
        call. = FALSE

                    		
                  

                  

                    169
                    
                    
                      
      )

                    		
                  

                  

                    170
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    171
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    172
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                  

                    173

translate_num_vec <- function(vec) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    183
                    2x

                    184
                    2x

                    185
                    2x
                    
                      
      seq(

                    2x
                    
                      
        strsplit(vec[i], ":")[[1]][1],

                    2x
                    
                      
        strsplit(vec[i], ":")[[1]][2]

                    		
                  

                  

                    188
                    
                    
                      
      ),

                    		
                  

                  

                    189
                    2x
                    
                      
      collapse = ", "

                    		
                  

                  

                    190
                    
                    
                      
    ), ")")

  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    192
                    1x
                    
                      
  vec

}

expand_trials_trial_seq <- function(object) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
  # Avoid NOTE for data.table

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    11x

                    11x

                    11x
                    
                      
  chunk_size <- object@expansion@chunk_size

                    13
                    11x
                    
                      
  keeplist <- unique(c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    11x
                    
                      
    "id", "trial_period", "followup_time", "outcome", "weight", "treatment",

                    11x
                    
                      
    outcome_adj_vars, object@outcome_model@treatment_var

                    		
                  

                  

                    16

                    17
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    11x
                    
                      
  wt <- NULL

                    4x

                    11x

                    23
                    !

                    11x
                    
                      
  } else if (chunk_size > 0) {

                    11x

                    13x

                    13x

                    33
                    13x
                    
                      
      minperiod = first_period,

                    11x
                    
                      
  object

#' @include te_model_fitter.R

                    163
                    4x

                    3x

                    165
                    3x
                    
                      
    "switch" = names(object@switch_weights@data_subset_expr),

                    		
                  

                  

                    166
                    3x

                    167

                    168
                    3x

                    169
                    2x
                    
                      
  expr <- object@switch_weights@data_subset_expr[[model]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    170

                    !

                    174
                    
                    
                      
  } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    175
                    1x
                    
                      
    object@data@data[, list(i = eval(expr))]

                    		
                  

                  

                    176
                    
                    
                      
  }

#' Case-control sampling of expanded data for the sequence of emulated trials

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' `r lifecycle::badge('stable')`

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' Perform case-control sampling of expanded data to create a data set of reduced size and calculate sampling weights

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' to be used in `trial_msm()`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' @param data_prep Result from [data_preparation()].

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' @param p_control Control sampling probability for selecting potential controls at each follow-up time of each trial.

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' @param subset_condition Expression used to [subset()] the trial data before case-control sampling.

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' @param sort Sort data before applying case-control sampling to make sure that the resulting data are identical when

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#'   sampling from the expanded data created with `separate_files = TRUE` or `separate_files = FALSE`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' @return A `data.frame` or a [split()] `data.frame` if  `length(p_control) > 1`. An additional column `sample_weight`

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#'   containing the sample weights will be added to the result. These can be included in the models fit with

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#'   [trial_msm()].

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#' # If necessary reduce the number of threads for data.table

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#' data.table::setDTthreads(2)

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#' data("te_data_ex")

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#' samples <- case_control_sampling_trials(te_data_ex, p_control = 0.01)

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
case_control_sampling_trials <- function(data_prep,

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
                                         p_control = NULL,

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
                                         subset_condition,

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
                                         sort = FALSE) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    8x
                    
                      
  assert_numeric(p_control, lower = 0, upper = 1, min.len = 1)

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    7x
                    
                      
  if (use_subset <- !missing(subset_condition)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    2x
                    
                      
    subset_expr <- substitute(subset_condition)

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    7x
                    
                      
  args <- alist(data_prep, p_control, use_subset, subset_expr, sort)

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    7x
                    
                      
  if (inherits(data_prep, "TE_data_prep_sep")) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    3x
                    
                      
    trial_samples <- do.call(sample_data_prep_sep, args)

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    4x
                    
                      
  } else if (inherits(data_prep, "TE_data_prep_dt")) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    3x
                    
                      
    trial_samples <- do.call(sample_data_prep_dt, args)

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
  } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    1x
                    
                      
    stop("Unknown data_prep object.")

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    6x
                    
                      
  if (length(p_control) > 1) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    1x
                    
                      
    split(rbindlist(trial_samples), by = "sample_id", keep.by = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
  } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    5x
                    
                      
    set(rbindlist(trial_samples), j = "sample_id", value = NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    
                    
                      
}

                    51

#' Sample from Period

                    		
                  

                  

                    91

                    92

                    93

                    97

                    107
                    21x

                    108
                    !

                    109
                    128x

                    128x
                    
                      
  all_samples <- lapply(p_control, function(p) {

#' Sample controls and cases from data subset by trial and follow-up time

                    		
                  

                  

                    122
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    123
                    
                    
                      
#' For the given data, find cases and sample a number of controls.

                    		
                  

                  

                    124
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    125
                    
                    
                      
#' @param data Data to sample from

                    		
                  

                  

                    126
                    
                    
                      
#' @param p_control Proportion of controls to select

                    		
                  

                  

                    127
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    128
                    
                    
                      
#' @return A data frame with the cases and the sampled controls

                    		
                  

                  

                    129
                    
                    
                      
#' @noRd

                    		
                  

                  

                    130
                    
                    
                      
do_sampling <- function(data, p_control = 0.01) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    131
                    
                    
                      
  ### cases occurred at each period and follow-up visit

                    		
                  

                  

                    132
                    24227x
                    
                      
  cases <- which(data$outcome == 1)

                    		
                  

                  

                    133
                    24227x
                    
                      
  ncase <- length(cases)

                    		
                  

                  

                    134
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    135
                    
                    
                      
  ### controls (still under follow-up and events haven't occurred) at each period and follow-up visit

                    		
                  

                  

                    136
                    24227x
                    
                      
  controls <- which(data$outcome == 0)

                    		
                  

                  

                    137
                    24227x
                    
                      
  n_controls <- length(controls)

                    		
                  

                  

                    138
                    24227x
                    
                      
  n_sample <- rbinom(1, n_controls, p_control)

                    		
                  

                  

                    139
                    24227x
                    
                      
  controlselect <- sample(controls, size = n_sample)

                    		
                  

                  

                    140
                    24227x
                    
                      
  dataall <- data[c(cases, controlselect), ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    141
                    24227x
                    
                      
  set(dataall, j = "sample_weight", value = c(rep(1, ncase), rep(1 / p_control, n_sample)))

                    		
                  

                  

                    142
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    143
                    24227x
                    
                      
  dataall

                    		
                  

                  

                    144
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                  

                    145
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    146
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    147

set_random_seed <- function(old_seed) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    200
                    30x
                    
                      
  if (is.null(old_seed)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    201
                    !
                    
                      
    rm(".Random.seed", envir = globalenv(), inherits = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    202
                    
                    
                      
  } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    203
                    30x
