#' Simulate Observational Data

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' Function to simulate observational data using the algorithm in Young and Tchetgen Tchetgen (2014)

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' @param ns number of subjects

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' @param nv no of visits including baseline visit

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' @param conf coefficient of X2 in the treatment and outcome models, controlling confounding strength of X2

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' @param treat_prev intercept of the treatment model, controlling overall treatment prevalence

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' @param all_treat (TRUE/FALSE)= enforcing treatments as if in an RCT

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' @param all_control (TRUE/FALSE)= enforcing non-treatments/control as if in an RCT

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' @param censor (TRUE/FALSE)= adding dependent censoring or not

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom stats ave rbinom rnorm

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#' @noRd

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
data_gen_censored <- function(ns,

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
                              nv,

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
                              conf = 0.5,

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
                              treat_prev = 0,

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
                              all_treat = FALSE,

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
                              all_control = FALSE,

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
                              censor = TRUE) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    5x
                    
                      
  assert_flag(all_treat)

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    5x
                    
                      
  assert_flag(all_control)

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    5x
                    
                      
  assert_flag(censor)

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    5x
                    
                      
  nvisit <- nv + 1

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    5x
                    
                      
  X1 <- rep(0, nvisit * ns) ## place holders for time-varying covariates

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    5x
                    
                      
  X2 <- rep(0, nvisit * ns) ## place holders for time-varying covariates

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    5x
                    
                      
  Z2 <- rnorm(nvisit * ns, 0, 1)

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    5x
                    
                      
  X3 <- rep(rbinom(ns, 1, 0.5), each = nvisit) # gender

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    5x
                    
                      
  X4 <- rep(rnorm(ns, 0, 1), each = nvisit) # baseline continuous covariate

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    5x
                    
                      
  age <- round(rnorm(ns, 35, 12), digits = 0) ## age at baseline

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    5x
                    
                      
  age <- rep(age, each = nvisit) + rep((-1):(nv - 1), ns) ## age at each visit

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    5x
                    
                      
  A <- rep(0, nvisit * ns) ## place holders for current  treatments

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    5x
                    
                      
  Ap <- rep(0, nvisit * ns) ## place holders for  previous treatments

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    5x
                    
                      
  CAp <- rep(0, nvisit * ns) ## place holders for sum of previous treatment A

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    5x
                    
                      
  Y <- rep(0, nvisit * ns) ## place holders for outcome vector

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    5x
                    
                      
  Yp <- rep(0, nvisit * ns) ## place holders for previous outcome vector

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
  ## Fill in initial values

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    5x
                    
                      
  seq1 <- seq(1, nvisit * ns - nv, nvisit)

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    5x
                    
                      
  X1[seq1] <- 0 ###  time-varying covariates at visit -1, by convention set at 0

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    5x
                    
                      
  X2[seq1] <- 0

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    5x
                    
                      
  P0 <- list() ## list of treatment probabilities

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    5x
                    
                      
  P0[[1]] <- rep(0, ns)

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    5x
                    
                      
  seqlist <- list()

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    5x
                    
                      
  seqlist[[1]] <- seq1

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    5x
                    
                      
  CAp[seq1] <- rep(0, ns)

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    5x
                    
                      
  for (k in 2:nvisit) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    
                    
                      
    ## update covariates

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    50x
                    
                      
    seqlist[[k]] <- seqlist[[k - 1]] + 1

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    50x
                    
                      
    Ap[seqlist[[k]]] <- A[seqlist[[k - 1]]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    50x
                    
                      
    CAp[seqlist[[k]]] <- CAp[seqlist[[k - 1]]] + Ap[seqlist[[k]]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    50x
                    
                      
    X1P0 <- 1 / (1 + exp(Ap[seqlist[[k]]]))

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    50x
                    
                      
    X1[seqlist[[k]]] <- rbinom(ns, 1, X1P0) ## binary time-varying confounder

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    50x
                    
                      
    X2[seqlist[[k]]] <- Z2[seqlist[[k]]] - 0.3 * Ap[seqlist[[k]]] ## continuous time-varying confounder

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    
                    
                      
    ## update treatment

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    50x
                    
                      
    lpp <- as.numeric(treat_prev) + Ap[seqlist[[k]]] + 0.5 * X1[seqlist[[k]]] + as.numeric(conf) * X2[seqlist[[k]]] -

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    50x
                    
                      
      0.2 * X3[seqlist[[k]]] + X4[seqlist[[k]]] - 0.3 * (age[seqlist[[k]]] - 35) / 12

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    50x
                    
                      
    P0[[k]] <- 1 / (1 + exp(-lpp))

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    50x
                    
                      
    if (all_treat) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    !
                    
                      
      A[seqlist[[k]]] <- 1.0

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    
                    
                      
    } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    50x
                    
                      
      if (all_control) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    !
                    
                      
        A[seqlist[[k]]] <- 0.0

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    
                    
                      
      } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    
                    
                      
        ## Generate treatment at current visit based on  covariates, previous treatment

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    50x
                    
                      
        A[seqlist[[k]]] <- rbinom(ns, 1, P0[[k]])

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    
                    
                      
    ## Generate outcome

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    50x
                    
                      
    lp <- -5 - 1.2 * A[seqlist[[k]]] + 0.5 * X1[seqlist[[k]]] + as.numeric(conf) * X2[seqlist[[k]]] +

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    50x
                    
                      
      X3[seqlist[[k]]] + X4[seqlist[[k]]] + 0.5 * (age[seqlist[[k]]] - 35) / 12

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    50x
                    
                      
    Yp[seqlist[[k]]] <- Y[seqlist[[k - 1]]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    50x
                    
                      
    Y[seqlist[[k]]] <- (rbinom(ns, 1, 1 / (1 + exp(-lp)))) * as.numeric(Yp[seqlist[[k]]] == 0) +

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    50x
                    
                      
      as.numeric(Yp[seqlist[[k]]] == 1)

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    
                    
                      
  ## Make data frame

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    5x
                    
                      
  ID <- rep(1:ns, each = nv)

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    
                    
                      
  ## Align data by removing values

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    5x
                    
                      
  NSEQ <- seq1

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    5x
                    
                      
  X1 <- X1[-NSEQ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    5x
                    
                      
  X2 <- X2[-NSEQ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    104
                    5x
                    
                      
  X3 <- X3[-NSEQ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    105
                    5x
                    
                      
  X4 <- X4[-NSEQ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    5x
                    
                      
  age <- age[-NSEQ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    5x
                    
                      
  A <- A[-NSEQ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    109
                    5x
                    
                      
  Ap <- Ap[-NSEQ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    110
                    5x
                    
                      
  CAp <- CAp[-NSEQ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    111
                    5x
                    
                      
  Y <- Y[-seq(1, nvisit * ns - nv, nvisit)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    112
                    5x
                    
                      
  Yp <- Yp[-seq(1, nvisit * ns - nv, nvisit)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    113
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    114
                    
                    
                      
  ## Create data frame

                    		
                  

                  

                    115

#' Robust Variance Calculation

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' This function performs the calculation of robust standard errors based on

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' variances estimated using [`sandwich::vcovCL`].

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' @param model The logistic regression model object.

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' @param data_id Values of id column of the data (ie `data[, id]`) to identify clusters.

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' @returns A list with elements `summary`, a table with the model summary using the

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' robust variance estimates, and `matrix`, the `sandwich` covariance matrix.

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' @keywords internal

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
robust_calculation <- function(model, data_id) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    10x
                    
                      
  var_matrix <- sandwich::vcovCL(

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    10x
                    
                      
    model,

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    10x
                    
                      
    cluster = data_id,

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    10x
                    
                      
    type = NULL,

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    10x
                    
                      
    sandwich = TRUE,

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    10x
                    
                      
    fix = FALSE

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    10x
                    
                      
  se <- sqrt(diag(var_matrix))

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    10x
                    
                      
  output <- data.frame(names = names(model$coefficients))

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    10x
                    
                      
  output$estimate <- model$coefficients

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    10x
                    
                      
  output$robust_se <- se[names(model$coefficients)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    10x
                    
                      
  output$`2.5%` <- output$estimate - (1.96 * output$robust_se)

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    10x
                    
                      
  output$`97.5%` <- output$estimate + (1.96 * output$robust_se)

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    10x
                    
                      
  output$z <- output$estimate / output$robust_se

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    10x
                    
                      
  output$p_value <- 2 * (1 - pnorm(abs(output$z)))

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    10x
                    
                      
  result <- list(summary = output, matrix = var_matrix)

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    10x
                    
                      
  class(result) <- "TE_robust"

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    10x
                    
                      
  result

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
}

                    51
                    
                    
                      
#' \eqn{sqrt{n}}-consistency estimation and valid inference of the parameters in marginal structural models for

                    		
                  

                  

                    52

#' \dontrun{

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    
                    
                      
#' if (

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    
                    
                      
#'   requireNamespace("parsnip", quietly = TRUE) &&

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    
                    
                      
#'     requireNamespace("rpart", quietly = TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    
                    
                      
#' ) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    
                    
                      
#'   # Use a decision tree model fitted with the rpart package

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    
                    
                      
#'   parsnip_model(

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    
                    
                      
#'     model_spec = parsnip::decision_tree(tree_depth = 30) |>

                    		
                  

                  

                    67

                    1
                    
                    
                      
#' A wrapper function to perform data preparation and model fitting in a sequence of emulated target trials

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' `r lifecycle::badge('stable')`

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' An all-in-one analysis using a sequence of emulated target trials. This provides a simplified interface to the main

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' functions [`data_preparation()`] and [`trial_msm()`].

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' @param data A `data.frame` containing all the required variables in the person-time format, i.e., the  `long' format.

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' @param id Name of the variable for identifiers of the individuals.  Default is `id'.

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' @param period Name of the variable for the visit/period.   Default is `period'.

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' @param treatment Name of the variable  for the treatment indicator at that visit/period. Default is `treatment'.

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#' @param outcome Name of the variable for the indicator of the outcome event at that visit/period.  Default is

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#'   `outcome'.

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' @param eligible Name of the variable for the indicator of eligibility for the target trial at that visit/period.

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#'   Default is `eligible'.

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#' @param outcome_cov A RHS formula with baseline covariates to be adjusted for in the marginal structural model for the

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#'   emulated trials. Note that if a time-varying covariate is specified in `outcome_cov`, only its value at each of the

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#'   trial baselines will be included in the expanded data.

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#' @param model_var Treatment variables to be included in the marginal structural model for the emulated trials.

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#'   `model_var = "assigned_treatment"` will create a variable `assigned_treatment` that is the assigned treatment at

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#'   the trial baseline, typically used for ITT and per-protocol analyses. `model_var = "dose"` will create a variable

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#'   `dose` that is the cumulative number of  treatments received since the trial baseline, typically used in as-treated

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#'   analyses.

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#' @param first_period First time period to be set as trial baseline  to start expanding the data.

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#' @param last_period Last time period to be set as trial baseline  to start expanding the data.

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#' @param first_followup First follow-up time/visit in the trials to be included in the marginal structural model for

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
#'   the outcome event.

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
#' @param last_followup Last follow-up time/visit in the trials to be included in the marginal structural model for the

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
#'   outcome event.

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
#' @param save_weight_models Save model objects for estimating the weights in `data_dir`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
#' @param analysis_weights Choose which type of weights to be used for fitting the marginal structural model for the

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
#'   outcome event.

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
#'  * `"asis"`: use the weights as calculated.

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
#'  * `"p99"`: use weights truncated at the 1st and 99th percentiles (based on the distribution of weights

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
#'   in the entire sample).

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      
#'  * `"weight_limits"`: use weights truncated at the values specified in `weight_limits`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
#'  * `"unweighted"`: set all analysis weights to 1, even if treatment weights or censoring weights were calculated.

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
#' @param weight_limits Lower and upper limits to truncate weights, given as `c(lower, upper)`

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
#' @param estimand_type Specify the estimand for the causal analyses in the sequence of emulated trials. `estimand_type

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    
                    
                      
#'   = "ITT"` will perform intention-to-treat analyses, where treatment switching after trial baselines are ignored.

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    
                    
                      
#'   `estimand_type = "PP"` will perform per-protocol analyses, where individuals' follow-ups are artificially censored

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
#'   and inverse probability of treatment weighting is applied. `estimand_type = "As-Treated"` will fit a standard

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      
#'   marginal structural model for all possible treatment sequences, where individuals' follow-ups are not artificially

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    
                    
                      
#'   censored  but treatment switching after trial baselines are accounted for by applying inverse probability of

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
#'   treatment weighting.
